\section{Introduction}
Combination function ,$^nC_r$ or $\binom{n}{r}$ is one of the basic function used in probability distribution, they are able to calculate the possible combination of $n$ object from $r$ object.

Standard normal distribution, often denote by the function $\phi(z)$ is the fundamental function to simplify complex integral of PDF which do not have elementary integral solve. How ever, the function $\phi(z)$ do not have elementary integral solve too. Therefore, in this report I am trying approximate $\phi(z)$  with combination.

I start doing research on this topic because of when I am researching about a identity about relationship between sine and combination, I try to change value of $n$ and $r$ in desmos. Then I soon realize that for some specific value of $n$ and $r$ the curve is peaked in $x=0$ and become closer and closer to zero in a wavy form. Afterward, I am learning 9709 paper 5, I learn about the standard normal distribution and realize is very similar to the curve that I have seen. That the reason why I start the research.

